data.title: Benjamín 'A' becomes league champion and Benjamín 'B' wins promotion
data.meta_description: Find out more about Benjamín 'A' becomes league champion and Benjamín 'B' wins promotion - C.D. Leganés - Official Website
data.text:
Triumphs for C.D. Leganés C, Juvenil B, Juvenil C, Infantiles and Alevines in a new weekend for pepinero grassroots soccer.

C.D. Leganés 'C'.

C.D. Leganés 'C' won against Atlético Valdeiglesias 2-1 by 0-1 in the match corresponding to the thirteenth day of Group 4 of First Regional. The team coached by Jonatan Di Giosa is in seventh position with 21 points, four points behind the leaders.

Juveniles

Sergio Solís' Juvenil A could not win in the second matchday of the División de Honor champions' phase against Rayo Vallecano (3-0).

Juvenil B, coached by Raúl Huertas, earned a point at the Jesús Polo Annex against Las Rozas C.F. 'A' in the match corresponding to the second day of the National Division promotion phase.

For their part, Juvenil C could not score in their match against R.C.D. Carabanchel 'A' (2-4) in the match corresponding to the thirteenth matchday of Group 2 of the First Autonomous Division. The team from Puebla is fourth with 25 points.

Cadets

Cadete A, coached by Álvaro Herradón, won against Unión Adarve 'A' (1-0) in the match corresponding to the thirteenth matchday of Group 1 of the First Autonomic Division. The pepineros are in third position with 29 points and have five wins in the last five matches.

Cadete B coached by Francisco Javier Fernández 'Kiko' could not score in their visit to Trival Valderas C.F. 'A' (3-2) in the match corresponding to the thirteenth matchday of Group 2 of the First Autonomic Division. Despite not scoring, the team from Puebla remains in twelfth position with 15 points.

Infantiles

José Luis Martín's Infantil A could not score in their match against Getafe C.F. 'A' (3-0) in the match corresponding to the thirteenth matchday. The Blue and Whites are in third place with 26 points, one point behind the second-placed team in Group 2 of the Honor Division.

For their part, the Infantil B team coached by Jara Cuenca won the three points by beating C.D. Los Yébenes-San Bruno 11-2 in the thirteenth matchday of the league. The pepinero team remains in third place with 29 points in Group 4 of the First Autonomous Division.

Alevines

Alevín A coached by Jesús Nova won against E.F.M.O. Boadilla 'A' (5-1) in the match corresponding to the thirteenth day of Group 4 of First Autonomic Division. The pepineros are leaders of their league with 34 points, with eleven wins and a draw.

Alevín B, coached by Rubén García, could not win in their visit to Getafe C.F. 'A' (3-0) in the thirteenth matchday of Group 3 of the First Autonomic Division. The Blue and Whites are in eighth position with 20 points.

Benjamins and Prebenjamín

The Benjamín A was proclaimed league champion of Group 16 of Preferente after beating Atlético de Madrid by 0-7 in the match corresponding to the eleventh matchday. The team coached by Alberto González has obtained 30 points out of a possible 30. For its part, Benjamin B also beat C.D. Inter Promesas 'A' by 5-2, which allows them to achieve promotion to the next category. The Prebenjamín A won the three points against E.F. Carabanchel (1-7) in the match corresponding to the eleventh matchday. The pepineros are in second place with 27 points.
